Extract columns that do not vary within variables in data

findCovs.Rd

Extract columns that do not vary within variables in data

findCovs(data, cols.id = NULL, as.fun = NULL)

Arguments

data

data.frame in which to look for covariates
cols.id

covariates will be searched for in combinations of values in these columns. Often cols.id will be either empty or ID. But it can also be both say c("ID","DRUG") or c("ID","TRT").
as.fun

The default is to return a data.table if data is a data.table and return a data.frame in all other cases. Pass a function in as.fun to convert to something else. See ?runAsFun.

Value

a data set with one observation per combination of values of variables listed in cols.id.

See also

Other DataCreate: NMorderColumns(), findVars(), flagsAssign(), flagsCount(), mergeCheck(), objInfo(), stampObj(), tmpcol()

Examples

dat <- NMscanData(system.file("examples/nonmem/xgxr001.lst", package = "NMdata"))
